00:06:19,588 --> 00:06:23,968
Just keep your eye on the judge as
much as possible... or on your dad and me.

77
00:06:24,051 --> 00:06:27,011
Don't give 'em any reason to
not like you. No faces. Okay?

78
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,007
You're doing great so far.

79
00:06:29,598 --> 00:06:30,718
You all are.

80
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:36,613
You see, this wasn't just
an average boy, the defendant.

81
00:06:37,523 --> 00:06:40,483
No, something set him apart.

82
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:43,532
His father.

83
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:46,867
A father who was the first
assistant district attorney.

84
00:06:46,949 --> 00:06:49,079
Top man, right here in this building.

85
00:06:50,786 --> 00:06:54,076
For years, the defendant watched his father

86
00:06:54,164 --> 00:06:57,464
prosecute every major
murder case in this county.

87
00:06:57,543 --> 00:07:02,973
He listened to dinner conversations.
Overheard phone calls, shop talk.

88
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:07,224
You might even say that
murder was the family business.

89
00:07:09,221 --> 00:07:12,021
But still, the question remains "Why?"

90
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:15,891
Why...

91
00:07:16,979 --> 00:07:20,399
