521
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:12,250
Your Honor, the defense
moves for a mistrial.

522
00:31:12,331 --> 00:31:14,142
- Oh, come on.
- He was given specific instructions.

523
00:31:14,166 --> 00:31:18,836
You are on extraordinarily thin ice,
Mr. Logiudice, you understand me?

524
00:31:18,921 --> 00:31:21,921
Now you wrap it up with
this witness right now.

525
00:31:22,007 --> 00:31:25,587
And if I hear even a whisper about the
defendant's grandfather going forward,

526
00:31:25,677 --> 00:31:27,717
Ms. Klein will get her
mistrial. Am I clear?

527
00:31:27,804 --> 00:31:30,314
Yes, Your Honor.

528
00:31:41,735 --> 00:31:43,025
Ladies and gentlemen,

529
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:48,330
there's a saying in the law,
"You cannot unring the bell"...

530
00:31:49,660 --> 00:31:54,500
but I am going to insist that you do
just that with regard to the last question.

531
00:31:57,084 --> 00:31:58,924
That must have
been torture for you...

532
00:32:00,087 --> 00:32:01,587
sitting on the sidelines.

533
00:32:02,464 --> 00:32:03,764
I had no choice.

534
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:07,045
So you trusted Ms. Klein?

535
00:32:07,845 --> 00:32:08,965
I did.

536
00:32:10,055 --> 00:32:13,725
On day four of the trial, the
Commonwealth called its final witness:

537
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,770
Derek Yoo.

538
00:32:16,854 --> 00:32:22,614
Did you feel that Ms. Klein adequately
prepared for Derek Yoo's testimony?

539
00:32:23,527 --> 00:32:25,027
Yeah, as best she could.

540
00:32:25,445 --> 00:32:27,815
She intended
to destroy his credibility?

541
00:32:28,282 --> 00:32:31,372
He had a plausible
motive. The jury had a right to know.

542
00:32:31,869 --> 00:32:33,409
What about you and Laurie?

543
00:32:35,622 --> 00:32:37,042
What about us?

544
00:32:38,333 --> 00:32:39,673
Were you prepared?

545
