575
00:35:46,897 --> 00:35:52,527
Which I got. I mean, Ben would
be a jerk to me too sometimes.

576
00:35:53,987 --> 00:35:56,237
At what point after Ben's murder

577
00:35:56,907 --> 00:35:59,197
did you begin to consider
your friend Jacob's role in it?

578
00:35:59,284 --> 00:36:00,704
Objection. Leading the witness.

579
00:36:02,079 --> 00:36:03,209
Overruled.

580
00:36:06,124 --> 00:36:08,044
You can go ahead and answer, young man.

581
00:36:08,752 --> 00:36:10,052
I guess it was three days later.

582
00:36:10,629 --> 00:36:14,879
Was there anything other than his
temper that began to make you suspicious?

583
00:36:14,967 --> 00:36:16,467
Well, yeah. The knife.

584
00:36:16,844 --> 00:36:19,724
Jake had this scary combat
knife he'd bought in town.

585
00:36:19,805 --> 00:36:22,975
- He used to bring it to school sometimes.
- To show it off, or... or what?

586
00:36:23,058 --> 00:36:26,348
Not really. I mean, he showed
it to me and our friend Dylan...

587
00:36:27,604 --> 00:36:30,074
but it was more like he
liked having it on him,

588
00:36:30,148 --> 00:36:31,358
walking around with it.

589
00:36:31,441 --> 00:36:34,571
Like... it was this secret thing he had.

590
00:36:35,028 --> 00:36:38,408
I see. So the bullying and the knife...

591
00:36:39,491 --> 00:36:41,371
But you knew about these things,

592
00:36:41,910 --> 00:36:44,540
and still, you didn't
suspect Jacob immediately?

593
00:36:46,081 --> 00:36:49,041
I don't know. Maybe
part of me did, a little.

594
00:36:50,294 --> 00:36:52,254
But it wasn't until I read
what he wrote online.

595
00:36:52,629 --> 00:36:53,799
Online?

596
00:36:53,881 --> 00:36:57,091
